{"Body":"<p>I am exploring of a possibility of experiencing the world around without a language. By listening, speaking, seeing and reflecting on words made by the alphabets of a language - one experiences the World. How far is this correct?</p>\n", "Id":"3200", "LastEditorUserId":"1021", "Title":"Can any one experience the World without a language? if yes to what extent, if no, why not?", "CreationDate":"2013-02-13T14:32:47.587", "OwnerUserId":"1759", "PostTypeId":"1", "Tags":"<philosophy-of-language><cognitive-linguistics><sapir-whorf-hypothesis>", "AnswerCount":"3", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2013-02-15T00:36:19.123", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"176", "WebsiteUrl":"https://launchpad.net/~replicator-snail", "ProfileImageUrl":"http://i.stack.imgur.com/KPUcH.png", "Id":"1021", "AccountId":"124682", "CreationDate":"2012-05-18T02:34:01.443", "AboutMe":"<p>. Native speaker of American English. Linux user. Familiar with several programming languages in the procedural, OO, and functional paradigms.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://codegolf.stackexchange.com/a/6855/2276\">Worst Code Golf ever</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://meta.stackoverflow.com/a/157374/146243\">New badge proposals!</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/fortune-mod/+bug/612986\" rel=\"nofollow\">Shakespeare bug in Ubuntu</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://meta.stackoverflow.com/questions/122120/the-great-question-deletion-audit-of-2012/122207#122207\">The Great Question Deletion Audit of 2012</a></strong></li>\n<li>Chat\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://chat.stackexchange.com/rooms/2495/terrifying-nightmare-monsters\">Horrible spiders</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://chat.stackexchange.com/rooms/2110/aww\">Adorable fluffy things</a></strong></li>\n<li><strong><a href=\"http://chat.stackexchange.com/rooms/1701/firearms\">LASERS!</a></strong></li>\n</ul></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Link_rot\" rel=\"nofollow\">Link rot</a> is evil. <a href=\"http://archive.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Archive</a> <a href=\"http://www.archiveteam.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">everything</a>. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keyboard_shortcut\" rel=\"nofollow\">The keyboard is king</a>. Correctness over performance. Canonicalize, normalize, deduplicate. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don%27t_repeat_yourself\" rel=\"nofollow\">Don't repeat yourself.</a> <a href=\"http://utf8everywhere.org/\" rel=\"nofollow\">UTF-8 > UTF-16.</a> Use <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Static_typing\" rel=\"nofollow\">static typing</a>: good for <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autocomplete\" rel=\"nofollow\">tooling</a>. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IKVM.NET\" rel=\"nofollow\">Re</a>-<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Open-source_software\" rel=\"nofollow\">use</a>; don't <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Not_invented_here\" rel=\"nofollow\">re</a>-<a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/reinvent_the_wheel\" rel=\"nofollow\">invent</a>. Correctness, then clarity, then concision and elegance. Play devil's advocate. First understand opponents' positions.</p>\n", "Location":"United States", "DownVotes":"7", "Views":"12", "Reputation":"1534", "DisplayName":"Mechanical snail", "LastAccessDate":"2013-06-02T04:51:14.103"}, "ViewCount":"214", "LastActivityDate":"2013-04-10T19:40:27.950", "Score":"-1", "CommentCount":"16", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"0", "DownVotes":"0", "Id":"1759", "AccountId":"1201176", "Views":"0", "Reputation":"2", "CreationDate":"2013-02-13T14:32:47.587", "DisplayName":"Charan Singh", "LastAccessDate":"2013-03-20T01:06:45.537"}}